init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I stood in the terminal for a few minutes, when a man dressed in a black suit and tie approached me.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He lead me to a private plane, with the license plate reading "The Flying White House".

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The man in the black suit opened the door for me, and I entered the plane.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The man in the black suit closed the door and told me to have a seat, "Mr. Kennedy will be here shortly".

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I sat down in a leather seat, and waited for JFK to arrive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I am gobsmacked, this is not a joke.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He sat down across from me and asked, "do you realize why I have called on you?".

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK told me that a threat of nuclear war is eminent and I must act accordingly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But JFK argued otherwise, he said that I was the only person who could handle this kind of job.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK dropped a folder on the table in front of me, and told me that he wanted me to read it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The pencil device was meant to be inserted into the center of the robot's CPU and it would cause him to crash and burn.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I made my way out of the airport, and to the nearest cab.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I pulled out the pencil device and asked him to sit in a chair.
